==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English [[mazer]], Old English [[maser]], from Old French [[masere]], a kind of maple wood, akin to Old High German [[masar]], German [[Maser]] "spot", and Icelandic [[mösurr]] "maple".

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪzə(r)|-eɪzə(r)]]

===Alternative spellings===
*[[maser]]

